  "original_title": "\u0db6\u0dab\u0dca\u0da9\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0d9c\u0db8\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dd4\u0dad\u0dca \u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1 \u0dc0\u0d82\u0da0\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dc4\u0dc3\u0dd4 \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A fuel fraud is also caught in Bandaragamin",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Bandaragama police say that two persons were arrested along with two cabs that were waiting in the queue near a petrol station in Bandaragama town to get petrol by falsely changing the fuel route between the engine and the fuel tank of two cabs and also changing the number plate in a fake manner.",
        "The police say that they found these two vehicles based on a confidential information received by the officers of the Western Province Intelligence Division attached to the Bandaragama Police that the registration number plates of two diesel-powered vehicles had been changed falsely and they were parked near the petrol station and in the middle of the queue.",
        "After arresting the two vehicles and the two drivers and bringing them to the police, the front of the two vehicles were opened and a further inspection was carried out. A plastic bottle filled with diesel was placed at the end of the engine section and connected to the engine through a pipe to start it up. A police officer said that he was able to see how."
      ],
